Reasoning: The paper deals with analyzing the computational complexity of solving puzzles in a video game, which involves algorithms and computational thinking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves analyzing the hardness of the puzzles, which can be related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The efficient algorithm for solving one of the puzzles suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the analysis of the puzzles' complexity can be related to game theory (cs.GT).
